originalText.text: The food here was really really really delicious. We had about three types of Naan-from garlic naan to the kind that has ground up lamb in the middle which was amazing. We also had the butter chicken and the mix grill sampler witha side of rice. The food was really quite amazing. The only downside was our water glasses were left empty and were not filled up with water and they never checked in to see how the food was, they just sort of dropped it off, no eye contact, and then even though it was just a party of two of us, they included a 20% gratuity which is fine in my opinion because I always tip 20% or more but I just thought it was interesting and I asked him if that was standard and they said yes that they add 20% gratuity whether it‚Äôs a party of 1, two, or 20 I don‚Äôt know if that‚Äôs true or not but that‚Äôs what they said.  Overall, good-okay experience but I don‚Äôt know if I will return on account of the service inside, but I would definitely order to go or for pick up because as stated before the flavors and food were incredible.

originalText.text: This place is in a great location and has good atmosphere. We had a variety of dishes (most pretty standard quality) with the palak paneer and garlic naan being particularly good. They are quick with bringing the food and Jaz the owner is lovely. One negative is they charge a 4% fee to use a card to pay although they do not advertise this until you receive the check. I also believe the food is slightly overpriced for the quality and quantity you receive.

originalText.text: Our reviews had over 34 million views so far this year.  We do not get paid we just love to eat and have fun.  We really love Jaz Indian Cuisine restaurant.  Just opened in early 2022 but already has a great reputation and was voted best resturant in Hell's Kitchen.  Well deserved.  We ate at the bar and the bartender was the owner "Jaz".  We explained we had rarely had Indian food so she designed our menu.  Not sure of all the things she ordered for us, but all of them were awesome.  We did get garlic Naan which is a thin fried flat bread that was great for dipping all of the food.  I had a lamb dish and Maria had a shrimp dish and a chicken dish.  All of them were full of flavor.  You tell them the heat amount you want.  We started at zero and went to 5.  We probably would have preferred 5 to 8 next time, but we wanted to start low just to be sure we were not overwhelmed.  The heat they use is full of flavor, which we really liked.  Be sure to get the fried onion things with green dipping sauce, they are super delicious.  I think they are called Onion Fritters.  Lovely.  We got 3 desserts that had names I could not pronounce.  All of them are really good.  Jaz is a great place and Jaz herself is fun to talk to as well as some of the regulars that sit at the bar.  About 20 tables but get a reservation to avoid the wait.  Full bar here and drinks were strong and reasonably priced.  Be sure to have Jaz suggest food and drinks, she is the best!!!!  Check out all of our reviews. If we do not like it we do no review it so all of the ones you see are places that are fantastic. Follow us if you like. We had over 36 million views so far this year and we thank you for that. We don't get paid, we just love to eat. Be sure to click on "RobH" at the top of this review to see all of them and to follow us if you like good food and FUN.  If we do a review it is because we love it.
